# UI conventions

## Stack

- **Tailwind CSS v4** for layout / spacing / colour. Prefer utility
  classes over hand-rolled CSS. The four themes (`epublate`,
  `textual-dark`, `textual-light`, `epublate-contrast`) live in
  `src/styles/theme.css`.
- **shadcn/ui** primitives in `src/components/ui/*`. Don't reinvent —
  if a primitive's variant is missing, extend it instead of forking.
- **Radix UI** under shadcn for dialogs, popovers, dropdowns.
- **`cn()` for class merging.** Import from `@/lib/utils`.

## Accessibility (Indeed A11y guidelines)

- Every interactive element is a `<button>` (or anchor). No
  `<div onClick>`.
- Provide `aria-label` for icon-only buttons; provide `title` so the
  tooltip surfaces on hover.
- Decorative glyphs use `aria-hidden`.
- Live status changes (e.g. "translating now" badge) include a
  textual count, not just a colour, so screen-reader users get the
  same signal.
- Keyboard-first: every screen registers its hotkeys with the
  cheat-sheet store (`?` / F1 surfaces them).

## Layout

- 12-column responsive grids; `min-w-0` and `min-h-0` on flex
  children that need to shrink.
- Persistent overflow uses `overflow-y-auto` on inner panes, not on
  `<body>`. The persistent batch status bar pins to the bottom.

```tsx
// ✅ icon button
<Button size="sm" variant="ghost" aria-label="Edit notes" title="Edit notes">
  <Pencil className="size-4" aria-hidden />
</Button>
```
